02/13/85  del_vol, dv

Syntax as a command:  dv drive_name


Function:  tells the system that a physical volume is no longer on a
drive.  This command can be used in ring 1 or ring 4.


Arguments:
drive_name
   has the form <subsys>_<nn>, e.g., dska_02.


Notes:  The drive specified may not contain part of an accepted logical
volume.  See the del_lv command for demounting logical volumes that are
in use.

The del_vol command can be used to cancel the assumed or known states
of any drives.
